        <!-- è¯­æ³• Tab -->
        <div class="tab-content" id="grammar-tab">
            <div class="card">
                <h2>è¯­æ³•è¦ç‚¹ Grammar Points</h2>
                
                <div class="grammar-points">
                    <div class="grammar-card">
                        <div class="grammar-header">1. é’Ÿç‚¹çš„è¡¨è¾¾ | Ways of Telling the Time</div>
                        <div class="grammar-body">
                            <p><strong>EspaÃ±ol:</strong> Formas de expresar la hora</p>
                            <p><strong>English:</strong> Ways of telling the time (hour)</p>
                            
                            <div class="grammar-example">
                                <p><strong>8:05</strong> å…«ç‚¹äº”åˆ†</p>
                                <p><strong>8:30</strong> å…«ç‚¹åŠ</p>
                                <p><strong>8:45</strong> å·®ä¸€åˆ»ä¹ç‚¹</p>
                            </div>
                            
                            <div class="grammar-example">
                                <p><strong>8:15</strong> å…«ç‚¹ä¸€åˆ»</p>
                                <p><strong>8:40</strong> å…«ç‚¹å››å</p>
                                <p><strong>8:55</strong> å·®äº”åˆ†ä¹ç‚¹</p>
                            </div>
                            
                            <div class="grammar-note">
                                <strong>EspaÃ±ol:</strong> Se usa "å·®" (chÃ ) para expresar minutos que faltan para la prÃ³xima hora. "ä¸€åˆ»" significa 15 minutos.
                            </div>
                            <div class="grammar-note">
                                <strong>English:</strong> "å·®" (chÃ ) is used to express minutes before the next hour. "ä¸€åˆ»" means 15 minutes (a quarter).
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="grammar-card">
                        <div class="grammar-header">2. æŒç»­æ—¶é—´çš„è¡¨è¾¾ | Ways of Telling the Duration of Time</div>
                        <div class="grammar-body">
                            <p><strong>EspaÃ±ol:</strong> Formas de expresar la duraciÃ³n del tiempo</p>
                            <p><strong>English:</strong> Ways of telling the duration of time</p>
                            
                            <div class="grammar-example">
                                <p>äº”åˆ†é’Ÿ (five minutes)</p>
                                <p>ä¸€åˆ»é’Ÿ (a quarter, 15 minutes)</p>
                                <p>ä¸€ä¸ªå°æ—¶ (one hour)</p>
                            </div>
                            
                            <div class="grammar-example">
                                <p>ä¸€å¤© (one day)</p>
                                <p>ä¸€ä¸ªæ˜ŸæœŸ (one week)</p>
                                <p>ä¸€ä¸ªæœˆ (one month)</p>
                                <p>ä¸€å¹´ (one year)</p>
                            </div>
                            
                            <div class="grammar-note">
                                <strong>EspaÃ±ol:</strong> Para expresar duraciÃ³n, se usa el nÃºmero + unidad de tiempo.
                            </div>
                            <div class="grammar-note">
                                <strong>English:</strong> To express duration, use number + time unit.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="grammar-card">
                        <div class="grammar-header">3. æ—¶é‡è¡¥è¯­ | Complement of Duration</div>
                        <div class="grammar-body">
                            <p><strong>EspaÃ±ol:</strong> Complemento de duraciÃ³n - indica cuÃ¡nto tiempo dura una acciÃ³n o estado</p>
                            <p><strong>English:</strong> A complement of duration placed after a verb shows the duration of an action or a state</p>
                            
                            <div class="grammar-example">
                                <p style="background: #E3F2F2; padding: 10px; border-radius: 5px; margin: 10px 0;">
                                    <strong>S V T</strong>
                                </p>
                                <p><strong>ä¾‹å¥ï¼š</strong>åæ±½è½¦è¦ ç”¨ ä¸€ä¸ªå°æ—¶ã€‚</p>
                                <p><strong>EspaÃ±ol:</strong> Tomar el coche requiere una hora.</p>
                                <p><strong>English:</strong> It takes one hour by car.</p>
                            </div>
                            
                            <div class="grammar-example">
                                <p><strong>ä¾‹å¥ï¼š</strong>ä»– è¯´äº†ååˆ†é’Ÿã€‚</p>
                                <p><strong>EspaÃ±ol:</strong> Ã‰l hablÃ³ durante diez minutos.</p>
                                <p><strong>English:</strong> He spoke for ten minutes.</p>
                            </div>
                            
                            <div class="grammar-note">
                                <strong>EspaÃ±ol:</strong> El complemento de duraciÃ³n se coloca despuÃ©s del verbo para indicar cuÃ¡nto tiempo dura la acciÃ³n.
                            </div>
                            <div class="grammar-note">
                                <strong>English:</strong> The complement of duration is placed after the verb to show how long the action lasts.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="grammar-card">
                        <div class="grammar-header">4. åŠ¨è¯é‡å¤ | Verb Repetition</div>
                        <div class="grammar-body">
                            <p><strong>EspaÃ±ol:</strong> RepeticiÃ³n del verbo con complemento de duraciÃ³n</p>
                            <p><strong>English:</strong> A verb can be repeated following its object. The repeated verb is followed by a complement of duration</p>
                            
                            <div class="grammar-example">
                                <p style="background: #E3F2F2; padding: 10px; border-radius: 5px; margin: 10px 0;">
                                    <strong>S V O V T</strong>
                                </p>
                                <p><strong>ä¾‹å¥ï¼š</strong>æˆ‘ å æ±½è½¦ åäº† ä¸€å¤©ã€‚</p>
                                <p><strong>EspaÃ±ol:</strong> TomÃ© el coche durante un dÃ­a.</p>
                                <p><strong>English:</strong> I took the car for one day.</p>
                            </div>
                            
                            <div class="grammar-note">
                                <strong>EspaÃ±ol:</strong> Cuando un verbo tiene un objeto, se repite el verbo despuÃ©s del objeto para aÃ±adir el complemento de duraciÃ³n.
                            </div>
                            <div class="grammar-note">
                                <strong>English:</strong> When a verb has an object, the verb is repeated after the object to add the duration complement.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="grammar-card">
                        <div class="grammar-header">5. "è·Ÿ......" ä»‹è¯çŸ­è¯­ | Prepositional Construction with "è·Ÿ"</div>
                        <div class="grammar-body">
                            <p><strong>EspaÃ±ol:</strong> La construcciÃ³n preposicional "è·Ÿ" y su objeto se usan frecuentemente delante del verbo como complemento adverbial</p>
                            <p><strong>English:</strong> The prepositional construction "è·Ÿâ€¦" and its object are often used in front of a verb as an adverbial adjunct</p>
                            
                            <div class="grammar-example">
                                <p style="background: #E3F2F2; padding: 10px; border-radius: 5px; margin: 10px 0;">
                                    <strong>S P O adv V O</strong>
                                </p>
                                <p><strong>ä¾‹å¥ï¼š</strong>æˆ‘ è·Ÿ æˆ‘çš„æœ‹å‹ ä¸€èµ· å» å•†åº—ã€‚</p>
                                <p><strong>EspaÃ±ol:</strong> Voy a la tienda con mi amigo.</p>
                                <p><strong>English:</strong> I go to the shop with my friend.</p>
                            </div>
                            
                            <div class="grammar-example">
                                <p><strong>ä¾‹å¥ï¼š</strong>ä»– è·Ÿ æˆ‘ è¯´ï¼š"æˆ‘ç°åœ¨å»ä¸Šè¯¾ã€‚"</p>
                                <p><strong>EspaÃ±ol:</strong> Ã‰l me dijo: "Ahora voy a clase."</p>
                                <p><strong>English:</strong> He said to me: "I'm going to class now."</p>
                            </div>
                            
                            <div class="grammarnote">
<strong>EspaÃ±ol:</strong> "è·Ÿ" significa "con" y se usa para indicar compaÃ±Ã­a o la persona a quien se dirige una acciÃ³n.
</div>
<div class="grammar-note">
<strong>English:</strong> "è·Ÿ" means "with" and is used to indicate accompaniment or the person to whom an action is directed.
</div>
</div>
</div>
                <div class="grammar-card">
                    <div class="grammar-header">6. "å‡ " çš„ç”¨æ³• | Usage of "å‡ "</div>
                    <div class="grammar-body">
                        <p><strong>EspaÃ±ol:</strong> "å‡ " se usa para preguntar sobre un nÃºmero menor que diez, o para indicar un nÃºmero no especificado</p>
                        <p><strong>English:</strong> "å‡ " is used to ask about a number smaller than ten. "å‡ " can also be used to indicate an unspecified number</p>
                        
                        <div class="grammar-example">
                            <p><strong>ç–‘é—®å¥ï¼š</strong>ä»Šå¤© æ˜ŸæœŸå‡ ï¼Ÿ</p>
                            <p><strong>EspaÃ±ol:</strong> Â¿QuÃ© dÃ­a de la semana es hoy?</p>
                            <p><strong>English:</strong> What day is today?</p>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="grammar-example">
                            <p><strong>é™ˆè¿°å¥ï¼š</strong>è¿™å‡ å¹´ï¼Œä»–ä»¬åœ¨ä¸­å›½æ–°å¼€äº†å‡ ä¸ªå¤§å•†åº—ã€‚</p>
                            <p><strong>EspaÃ±ol:</strong> En estos aÃ±os, han abierto varias tiendas grandes en China.</p>
                            <p><strong>English:</strong> In recent years, they have opened several large stores in China.</p>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="grammar-note">
                            <strong>EspaÃ±ol:</strong> "å‡ " se usa en preguntas para nÃºmeros del 1-9, y en oraciones afirmativas para indicar "varios" o "algunos".
                        </div>
                        <div class="grammar-note">
                            <strong>English:</strong> "å‡ " is used in questions for numbers 1-9, and in statements to mean "several" or "a few".
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <!-- ç»ƒä¹  Tab -->
    <div class="tab-content" id="exercises-tab">
